$ PHP code snippets

Related to → development/web/php/snippets/string[strings]

Related to → development/web/php/snippets/array[Arrays]

An → development/web/php/snippets/array/associative[associative array] allows to store key/value pairs.

→ development/web/php/snippets/list[`list($foo, $bar, $baz) = $someArray;`] assigns elements of an array to individual variables.

→ development/web/php/snippets/__FILE__[`__FILE__`] expands to the absolute path of the file where this identifier occurs.
-
→ development/web/php/snippets/__LINE-FILE-DIR__[`__LINE__` and `__DIR__`], in a similar spirit, expand to the line number and the directory name.

→ development/web/php/snippets/_SERVER[`$_SERVER`]

→ development/web/php/snippets/_GET[`$_GET`] is an → development/web/php/snippets/array/associative[associative array] whose key/value pairs contain the values of *query strings*.

→ development/web/php/snippets/date-time[Date and time related]

→ development/web/php/snippets/htmlspecialchars[`htmlspecialchars`] converts characters that have a meaning in → development/web/HTML to → development/web/HTML/entities.

→ development/web/php/snippets/getenv[`getenv('VARNAME')`] returns the value of the → development/environment-variable[environment variable] `VARNAME`.

→ development/web/php/snippets/null-empty[`null`, `empty()` …]

→ development/web/php/snippets/HTTP/header[`header()`] sends a specific → development/web/HTTP/header.

Related to the → development/web/php/snippets/function[`function`] statement.

Related to the → development/web/php/snippets/variable[variables].

Managing → development/web/php/snippets/session[sessions]

→ development/web/php/snippets/including-files[Including files].


